The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 30 September is 3,492 (404.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 26 September, there were 136 new confirmed cases (15.7 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 19 September, there were 114 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 19% (22 extra cases).
